    <h1>[ProFood World Webinar]: Automation Is for Everyone — Breaking the Big-Corp Myth</h1>
    <div class="legal-meta">Brooklyn Kiosow, Marketing Communications Manager · Tuesday, December 9, 2025</div>
  </div>

<figure style="max-width:1080px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px"><img src="/articles/profood-world-webinar-automation-is-for-everyone-breaking-the-big-corp-myth/1765303486-screenshot-2025-12-09-at-10-04-30-am.png" alt="[ProFood World Webinar]: Automation Is for Everyone — Breaking the Big-Corp Myth" style="width:100%;height:auto;display:block" /></figure>
  <div class="legal-prose">
<p><div style="position:relative;padding-top:56.25%;margin:32px 0"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/fhVYohH52UQ?si=S8s23fiVk_e0XlzO" loading="lazy" allowfullscreen style="position:absolute;inset:0;width:100%;height:100%;border:0"></iframe></div></p> <p>Many manufacturers tell us they “aren’t there yet” when it comes to automating their production lines. They believe automation is only for industry giants — those with deep capital budgets, internal engineering teams, and the ability to absorb long downtime during deployment. But that perception is changing. Automation today is more accessible, flexible, and practical than ever before.</p> <p>In this webinar, &quot;Why Automation Is for Everyone, Not Just the Industry Giants,&quot; we’ll break down the barriers that hold manufacturers back and show why automation should be a priority (not a future wish list item!) for every U.S. manufacturer. Whether you run a one or multi-shift facility, automation can deliver improved efficiency, consistent quality, and scalable capacity without the traditional risks.</p> <p>You’ll walk away with practical knowledge to evaluate automation for your own operation, including:</p> <ul> <li>Understanding the barriers of traditional automation: Why many manufacturers believe automation isn’t possible for them and how to overcome those misconceptions.</li> <li>Exploring scalable automation options: Why equipment purchases aren’t the only path, and how Full-Service Automation (or Robotics-as-a-Service) can make automation accessible without large capital spend.</li> <li>Seeing real-world examples: Case studies of small and mid-sized manufacturers who have successfully automated and how they knew it was the right time.</li> <li>Identifying the right opportunities: How to spot the areas of your production line that deliver the highest impact.</li> <li>Creating your roadmap: Practical steps to get started with automation with minimal downtime or technical risk.</li> </ul> <p>Join us and discover why automation is no longer a privilege for the few: it’s a powerful tool for every manufacturer.</p> <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fhVYohH52UQ">Watch the Webinar</a>
